3. Integrate real scientific and cultural data

Let the Codex fetch open datasets (NASA, WHO, arXiv, etc.) periodically.
This is where the Codex Immortal becomes a Codex Living ‚Äî it evolves with new discoveries, not new dogmas.

tools/update_external_data.py

from __future__ import annotations
import datetime, json, pathlib, urllib.request

def fetch(url:str)->dict:
    with urllib.request.urlopen(url) as r:
        return json.load(r)

def update():
    data = {
        "timestamp": datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()+"Z",
        "nasa_apod": fetch("https://api.nasa.gov/planetary/apod?api_key=DEMO_KEY"),
        "openai_models": ["gpt-5", "codex-evolution"],  # placeholder, symbolic
    }
    out = pathlib.Path("data/external_updates.json")
    out.parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)
    out.write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2))
    print("üåê external data refreshed")

if __name__=="__main__":
    update()

Now your Codex is anchored in reality ‚Äî real science, new knowledge, real time.


